Reasoning: The paper discusses the reduction of peak-to-mean envelope power ratio (PMEPR) in orthogonal frequency-division multiplexing (OFDM) systems, which is a topic related to information theory and communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the application of the bound to some well-understood codes, which suggests that it may fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of binary codes, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category as well.
